		"description": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-02ef8d1c-7fff-52f4-c1e4-316986923a83\" dir=\"ltr\">Your investigation into your magical ancestry has borne useful fruit, unlocking useful magical tricks and further enhancing your already considerable intellect. You gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\">When you cast a divination spell, you can spend 1 sorcery point and choose yourself or another creature you can see. It gains advantage on its next Intelligence check or saving throw. If the target finishes a rest before using this benefit, it is lost. A creature can only have one instance of this benefit at a time.&nbsp;</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You gain an expertise die on Deception and Persuasion checks against creatures of your ancestry type.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You are a speed reader; you can read a page of un-ciphered text in a language you know in a round.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Half your sorcerer levels count as scholar levels for the purpose of gaining the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.jet01i63abb2v66h]{Measure Twice, Cut Once} feature.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Your Scholar levels count as sorcerer levels for the purpose of determining your maximum number of sorcery points.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You can spend 9 sorcery points and suffer a level of strife to gain an additional use of Measure Twice, Cut Once if it is expended.</li></ul>",
